In article <930519.140856.2k3.rusnews.w165w@mantis.co.uk> mathew <mathew@mantis.co.uk> writes:
>The install program for 4DOS (an excellent replacement for DOS's
>COMMAND.COM) requires a key which depends upon your organization name.  So I
>couldn't use Mantis's key to illegally "unlock" a copy without having
>"Mantis Consultants" burned into it.

A few years ago a group of us were discussing ways of doing this for
game software.  What we came up with was using a key of...  Your name
credit and card number.  That way, a user would not be likely to
give that out to "everyone".


